(998, 61, 'add_country_4_content_section', '<b>TOURIST VISA</b><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><b>\r\n</b></span></span>01. Original passport, valid for at least six months after the intended arrival to Brazil. The passport must be signed and have at least 2 blank visa pages. (Please note: soiled, damaged or defaced passports will not be accepted. Obtain a new passport if your current one does not meet such criteria.)\r\n02. Old passport, whenever available.\r\n03. One recent photo, size 4cm x 5cm, in colour, front view, white background.\r\n04. Original Personal Cover Letter on company letterhead with relevant information about the applicant and the intended trip\r\n05. If Employee Original NOC from Employer\r\n06. Last 03 months Original Payslip\r\n07. Last 03 Years ITR Personal\r\n08. Last 03 months Original updated bank statement Personal\r\n09. Flight tickets (booked itinerary showing entrance into and exit from Brazil)\r\n10. Hotel reservation or similar document\r\n11. Covid Final Vaccination Certificate\r\n12. Applicant personal contact number  mandatory\r\n\r\n<b>BRAZIL BUSINESS VISA</b>\r\n\r\n1. Original passport, valid for at least six months after the intended arrival to Brazil. The passport must be signed and have at least 2 blank visa pages. (Please note: soiled, damaged or defaced passports will not be accepted. Obtain a new passport if your current one does not meet such criteria.)\r\n\r\n2. Old passport, whenever available.\r\n\r\n3. One recent photo, size 4cm x 5cm, in colour, front view, white background.\r\n\r\n4. Original dispatch letter from the applicant\'s employer, addressed to the consular service of the Embassy of India in New Delhi, including the following information:\r\n\r\n* The employee\'s name and title;\r\n\r\n* Time of service for the company;\r\n\r\n* Monthly salary paid by the company to the applicant;\r\n\r\n* Contact person in Brazil;\r\n\r\n* Description of the business activities to be performed in a very clear, specific and detailed manner (generic descriptions might lead to delays and require the applicant to provide additional information and/or to appear for an interview at the Embassy);\r\n\r\n* Intended duration of the stay;\r\n\r\n* Statement that the company shall assume full responsibility for the applicant while in Brazil and that the applicant will not exceed the legally authorized stay per visit;\r\n\r\n* Statement that the company will bear all the costs with the trip;\r\n\r\n* Signature and stamp by a senior manager;\r\n\r\n5. One-page invitation letter (original with signature notarized in Brazil - \"autenticada em cartrio\") in Portuguese from a Brazilian company addressed to the consular service Embassy of Brazil in New Delhi, including the following information:\r\n\r\n* The name and the position that the applicant holds in the company;\r\n\r\n* clear, specific and detailed purpose of the trip and business activities which will be performed in Brazil.\r\n\r\n* stamp the CNPJ number (tax registration code), address and telephone number of the Brazilian company.\r\n\r\n6. Print out of itinerary of a confirmed round trip ticket with the hotel reservation\r\n\r\n7. If the applicant is self-employed:\r\n\r\n* bank letter stating his/her financial references; and\r\n\r\n* notarized Copy of the companys registration.\r\n\r\n* In the case of a professional trader or investor, provide notarized brokerage notes for the last 6 (six) months.\r\n\r\n8. If the applicant is Employe:\r\n\r\n* Last 03 months Original updated Personal Bank Statement\r\n\r\n* Last 02 years ITR\r\n\r\n* Last 03 months Original salary slip with signing authority signature &amp; stamp\r\n\r\n9. Company Last 03 months Original updated Bank Statement\r\n\r\n10. Company Last 02 years ITR\r\n\r\n11. Covid Final Vaccination Certificate\r\n\r\n12. Applicant personal contact number - mandatory'),
