(1160, 61, 'add_country_31_content_section', 'A Schengen visais a short-stay visa that allows a person to travel to any members of theSchengen Areaper stays up to 90 days for tourism or business purposes.\r\n\r\n<b>Schengen visa Documents list:</b>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><b>Original Valid passport for 06 months from the date of travel + Old passport.</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>2 photographs: 35 X 45 cm, white background matt finish, 80% face size.</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Return ticket.</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Travel Insurance</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Income tax papers for last 03 yrs or Form 16.</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Original saving Bank Statements last 6 months updated</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Salary Slips for last 3 months - if employed</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Original Leave Letter on Company letterhead - if employed</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Retire proof /Pension order- if retired</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Business Registration  if self-employed</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>hotel booking with all passenger name...</b></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<u><b>Documents from Friends/Relatives Visiting Schengen Area:</b></u>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><b>Passport &amp; Visa copies Invitation letter</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Bank statement last 3 months</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Last 3 months payslip.</b></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;'),
